{
  "texts": [
    "All the relevant ethical principles that apply to data science and machine learning research were observed in this work.",
    "The causal graph in our framework includes four variables: interventions (treatments T), observations (images O), outcomes (phenotypes Y) and confounders (e.g. batches C).",
    "Each of the nodes in the graph is a random variable with an associated probability distribution, which is unknown.",
    "Table 3 summarizes the assumptions made in practice for each variable.",
    "The exact cardinality of each variable depends on the dataset of focus."
  ]
}